</FOOTNAME>
<!-- PJG ITAG l=28 g=1 f=1 -->
The Agency analyzed many cash-flow ratios, some of which subtracted a constant amount (e.g., $5 million, $10 million,
$15 million), others of which, like the ratio in Test 94, subtracted variable amounts. Of the ratios that subtracted
a constant amount, this ratio, which subtracted $10 million, was the most effective in reducing public and private
costs.
